This paper deals with the complexity of reasoning in default logic, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also involves the classification of Boolean functions, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses complexity classes such as SigmaP2, DeltaP2, NP, P, and NL, which are related to computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper involves the study of sets and lattice structures, which are topics in discrete mathematics and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with propositional connectives, which are part of the field of programming languages and compilers (cs.PL).
